servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lemon{1}. Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}; chop into bite-size pieces. Thinly slice @tomato{1} into rounds; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pat @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season all over with half the @Italian seasoning{1/2%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together @Caesar dressing{1.5%ounce}, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, @Italian seasoning{1/2%teaspoon}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

> Be sure to measure the Italian Seasoning—we sent more!

In a #large bowl{}, massage kale using your hands (similar to how you would knead dough) until leaves are tender, ~{1%minute}.

> Don't skip this step—massaging helps the kale leaves wilt slightly, lending a tender (never fibrous!) texture.

To bowl with kale, add half the creamy Caesar dressing; toss to coat. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Wrap @flour tortillas{2} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Place tortillas on a clean work surface. Spread remaining creamy Caesar dressing across bottom third of each tortilla. Top with chicken, tomato, half the @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}, and as much kale salad as you like (be sure to reserve some salad for serving!).

Fold up bottom side of each tortilla over filling, then fold over left and right sides toward filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to form wraps.

Halve wraps on a diagonal; divide wraps and remaining kale salad between plates. Garnish salad with remaining Parmesan and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.